cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the design and implementation of an orchestration layer for virtual middleboxes in cloud environments. This involves addressing challenges related to network dynamics, traffic engineering, and scaling strategies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security benefits, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of cloud environments and virtualization technologies points towards cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions software-defined networking mechanisms, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
